 - - name: African iron overload
- type: disease
- source: MONDO
- details:
  - mondo_name: African iron overload
  - mondo_definition: African iron overload is a rare disorder described in sub-Saharan African populations and is characterized by iron overload due to excess dietary iron intake and possibly genetic factors, leading to hepatic portal fibrosis and micronodular cirrhosis.
  - umls_description: Disorders in the processing of iron in the body: its absorption, transport, storage, and utilization. 
  - orphanet_definition: A rare disorder described in sub-Saharan African populations and characterized by iron overload due to excess dietary iron intake and possibly genetic factors, leading to hepatic portal fibrosis and micronodular cirrhosis.

- - name: genetic hyperferritinemia without iron overload
- type: disease
- source: MONDO
- details:
  - mondo_name: genetic hyperferritinemia without iron overload
  - mondo_definition: Genetic hyperferritinemia without iron overload is a rare biological anomaly defined as high serum ferritin levels without elevations of transferrin saturation, tissue or serum iron and characterized by an apparently asymptomatic clinical phenotype.
